HEADWORD: Citadel
<hw>Cit"a*del</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>citadelle</ets>, It. <ets>citadella</ets>, di<?/. of
<ets>citt<?/</ets> city, fr. L. <ets>civitas</ets>. See
<er>City</er>.]</ety> <def>A fortress in or near a fortified city,
commanding the city and fortifications, and intended as a final point of
defense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Syn</b></col>. -- <cd>Stronghold. See
<er>Fortress</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

